<p>Port Said<br/>4th December 1914</p>
<p>My dear Father &amp; Mother.<br/>I expect you will be surprised at not hearing from me from Aden, especially when I told Pat I was writing but there was no opportunity of getting more letters ashore so I had to let it slide until now.<br/>We stayed a day longer in Colombo than we expected owing to the ship requiring water, and for this reason we had to go in to the Inner Harbour and consequently saw a little more of the Town. Five days sail from Colombo brought us to Aden. This is a rather dull place, being merely a coaling station and the only points of interest are the splendid British fortifications there, now manned by Territorial troops, the</p>
